<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pot" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pot,</orth> a vessel more deep than broad, used for several purposes: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.930" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 930</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.930" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 930</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 1.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 1.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 6</bibl> <cit><quote>(a little p. and soon hot).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.233" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 233</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.10.16" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 10, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 9</bibl>. <cit><quote>they have shut him in. To the p., I warrant him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.4.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 4, 47</bibl></cit> (i. e. to destruction, to certain death; cf. the German: <emph>in die Pfanne gehauen werden</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>